The Australian government strongly opposes Japanese whaling in the Antarctic whale sanctuary, pushing for a ban on all forms of whaling.
Prime Minister Howard challenges Japan's claim of needing to expand whale kills for research, highlighting the economic value of whale watching in Australia.
Despite diplomatic efforts, Japan remains firm on continuing whaling for research purposes.
Australia and New Zealand are exploring legal avenues to stop Japan's increased whale hunt, fearing a potential majority shift in the International Whaling Commission.
The battle against whaling continues through diplomatic channels and potential legal actions to protect endangered whale species.
